-- Credit Agricole Said to Tender for Tier 1, Upper Tier 2 Notes
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-01-26T13:35:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-26/credit-agricole-said-to-tender-for-tier-1-upper-tier-2-notes.html
Credit Agricole SA (ACA)  is offering to
buy back Tier 1 and Upper Tier 2 notes with a face value of as
much as 2.1 billion euros, according to a banker with knowledge
of the transaction.  The offer, which starts today and expires on Feb. 3, covers
seven securities denominated in euros, pounds and Canadian
dollars, the banker said. The tender prices range from 52
percent of face value to 79 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
